race.comment: IMPENDING FURY (6) finds it tough to get off the mark but it certainly hasn't been without trying. Missed narrowly two back at Gawler, then turned in another solid effort when fourth at the latest. Only needs to hold his form to break through this time. EMBERANCE (8) has been better in her last two and can keep the ball rolling. Gets in light with the claim, though will need some luck from the wide draw. CAER IBORMEITH (7) looks ready for the rise in trip and should be hitting her straps now. Drawn well and rates among the main chances. KOHALA (3) warmed nicely late at Murray Bridge. Should be further improved and is in the mix.
